    "body": "You can already do this by writing your own `prompt` function and putting it in your profile so that it is available every time you start PowerShell. For example:\r\n```\r\nfunction prompt() {\r\n    \"`e[48;2;255;64;64m`e[38;2;0;0;0mPS `e[4m$($executionContext.SessionState.Path.CurrentLocation)`e[24m$('>' * ($nestedPromptLevel + 1))`e[0m \"\r\n}\r\n```\r\nFor more info on what VT sequences you can use, see: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/console-virtual-terminal-sequences\r\n\r\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/media/logos/logo-ms-social.png\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><strong><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/console-virtual-terminal-sequences\">Console Virtual Terminal Sequences - Windows Console</a></strong></div><div>Virtual terminal sequences are control character sequences that can control cursor movement, colorÀøont mode, and other operations when written to the output stream.</div></blockquote>",
